name: Arches National Park
description: The Arches were amazing! The national park was a little hot, but the views were extremely amazing.

name: Yosemite National Park
description: Yosemite National Park was extremely vast. The tall mountains and the green trees are a sight to see. Not to mention the waterfalls! Will definitely return to this park again.

name: Zion National Park
description: At the top of the hike, there is a place called Angel's landing. It was kind of dangerous to climb up, and I had to hold on the chains that were connected to the side of the walls to climb up the side of the mountain. The view at the top was unmatched by any other National Park I have been to!

name: Rocky Mountain National Park
description: It's as rocky as they say it is! I tripped over a rock on while hiking around this area and had to be helicopter off the side of the mountain! Let's hope my medical insurance covers these costs, but I highly doubt it.

name: Joshua Tree National Park
description: Joshua Tree National Park was extremely hot. I felt like I was going to die. I felt like I was an egg frying on a hot stove. Maybe I'll come back in the winter when its cooler.

name: Redwood National and State Parks
description: I felt so tiny next to all these Redwoods! They're the biggest trees I have ever seen. Definitely come back next summer for. It was one of my favorite national parks I have been to.

name: Death Valley National Park
description: They call it Death Valley for a reason...

name: Sequoia & Kings Canyon National Park
description: We dipped in the lake. It was nice and cold. Best trip ever.
